agments pertaining to Choerilus of Iasus, updating and expanding the latest collection edited by H. Lloyd-Jones and P. Parsons in the Supplementum Hellenisticum (1983). Following up, the book develops in four chapters an analysis and discussion of the texts collected in the critical edition. The fifth concluding chapter retraces and contextualises the history of modern studies, from the Renaissance on, concerning the elusive figure of Choerilus.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aChoerilus von Iasus. 4aEpische Dichtung. 4aHellenismus. 4aTextkritik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAlexander the Great.  aHellenistic poetry.  afragmentary literature.  atextual criticism.0 cEPUBz97831107470890 cprintz978311074660040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074704140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110747041423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110747041/original  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK